    <div class="intro" style = "margin-left:160px ;"  ><em><!-- space the text 160px from the left--> 
      Amia Nut Company Limited was incorporated in 2011 primarily to engage in agro-food processing and more particularly to exploit the opportunity that existed in the Kenyan macadamia nut market.

The company began with a modest processing facility in Thika, Kiambu county. Over the years, the company has grown and has relocated to a state of the art facility that is located in Maragua, Muranga County. The head offices are located in Parklands, Nairobi from which administration and logistics work is done.

Our core business is the processing of macadamia nuts and macadamia oil to export markets.

Our mission

To add value to local agricultural output by engaging in food processing using modern technology to ensure high quality produce for export markets.

Our Vision

To be the leading macadamia nut processor in Kenya.

Core Values

Integrity, Trust, Accountability, Constant Improvement, Quality, Teamwork, Innovation.

Strategic Partners

In order to ensure that we meet the global demand of high quality macadamia nuts, Afrimac has developed strategic partners through the years. These partners share the same values, business ethos and processing standards as we do. They are spread out in the different macadamia growing regions in Kenya, giving them easier access to <b>farmers.</b>
    </em></div>
